 {"id":"bd-yx9r.5.3","title":"Port obligation, record, session, and link public parity","description":"Rust exposes rich obligation and record families plus session and link surfaces used for diagnostics, proofs, and long-lived coordination. ANSI C currently has only partial lower-level pieces, leaving a large user-facing and correctness-story gap.","design":"Implement public record types, obligation helpers beyond the raw kernel path, and session/link coordination APIs. Keep observability, monitor, and evidence-sink work in a dedicated sibling task so this bead stays implementable without losing scope.","acceptance_criteria":"A. The missing public record, obligation, session, and link module families exist and integrate with runtime flows.\\nB. Tests cover record lifecycle, session/link behavior, and obligation misuse.\\nC. At least one e2e or smoke lane exercises a realistic session/link flow with detailed logs and failure summaries.","notes":"Coordinate with the new observability/evidence task under the same epic so proof artifacts and runtime records share one coherent contract.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:22.799210276Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-14T20:52:58.448641833Z","closed_at":"2026-03-14T20:52:58.448232799Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","evidence","obligation","record","session"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:53.754722768Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:54.563725663Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:55.384692776Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id